==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Ruddle
<hw>Rud"dle</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A riddle or sieve.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Holland.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ruddle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Ruddle
<hw>Rud"dle</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Rud</er>; cf.
<er>Reddle</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A species of red earth
colored by iron sesquioxide; red ocher.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ruddle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Ruddle
<hw>Rud"dle</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To mark with ruddle; to raddle;
to rouge.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Their <xex>ruddled</xex> cheeks.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Thackeray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A fair sheep newly <qex>ruddled</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Lady M. W.
Montagu.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ruddock</ent>⟦br⟧
